1. Welcome to Your New Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern

We are thrilled that you have chosen to invest in our Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern. This exceptional product, manufactured by the esteemed Sunglow brand, is designed to bring radiance and durability to your outdoor experiences. In this manual, we shall familiarize you with the features and functions of your new solar lantern, as well as provide instructions on its optimal utilization.


1.1 Overview of Key Features

The Revive XL Solar Lantern boasts a brightness level of up to 30 lumens, making it an ideal companion for camping excursions and outdoor adventures. It is equipped with a high-capacity rechargeable battery, which can be replenished through exposure to sunlight or by connecting it to a USB power source. This solar lantern also offers the convenience of an adjustable brightness control feature, allowing users to customize lighting levels according to their preferences and environmental conditions.

1.2 Unboxing Your Solar Lantern


Upon receiving your Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern, please find the following items within the packaging:


The lantern itself A USB charging cable User manual (this document)


1.3 Preparing Your Solar Lantern for Use

Before first use, ensure that your solar lantern is fully charged by leaving it in a sunlit area or connecting it to a USB power source. Familiarize yourself with the various components and controls of your lantern as described below:

Power switch: Located on the base of the lantern. Press to turn on/off the device. Brightness control button: Positioned near the bottom of the solar panel, press this button to cycle through various brightness settings.

We hope that you enjoy your new Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern and that it illuminates many memorable moments during your adventures. Should you have any questions or

2. Product Overview and Features


2.1: Product Description

The Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern (referred to hereafter as "the Lantern") is an exceptional solar-powered lantern, meticulously crafted by the esteemed brand, Sunglow. Designed for those seeking a radiant and durable companion for their outdoor expeditions, this lantern is a must-have accessory for camping trips and adventure activities. The Revive XL Solar Lantern offers an alluring illumination, recharging effortlessly under sunlight or through USB power sources (Fig. 1).

Diagram illustrating the solar panels on top of the lantern


Figure 1: The Revive XL Solar Lantern boasting its integrated solar charging panels.


2.2: Brightness Adjustment

To cater to various illumination preferences and surroundings, the Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern comes equipped with an adjustable brightness function. Users may toggle between three distinct levels of luminosity (Fig. 2) by pressing and holding the designated button for a few seconds until their desired setting is reached.

Diagram showing the location and appearance of the brightness adjustment button


Figure 2: Locating the brightness adjustment button on the Revive XL Solar Lantern.


2.3: Battery Life and Charging


2.3.1: Solar Charging

The Revive XL Solar Lantern harnesses the power of sunlight for its primary energy source, offering an impressive battery life span. Given optimal sun exposure, the lantern's batteries will naturally recharge, ensuring a consistent illumination experience.

2.3.2: USB Charging

In addition to solar charging capabilities, the Revive XL Solar Lantern also supports USB charging for added flexibility and convenience. Utilize this feature when the lantern is not being exposed to direct sunlight, or during extended periods of cloudy weather, ensuring your lantern remains illuminated at all times (Fig. 3).

2.4: Durability and Weather Resistance

Engineered with high-quality materials, the Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern guarantees enduring durability, making it an indispensable piece of equipment for outdoor enthusiasts. Its sturdy construction can withstand harsh weather conditions, including rain, humidity, and extreme temperatures (Fig. 4).

## 3. Setup and Installation

Upon receiving your esteemed Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern, we extend our most sincere appreciation for your selection of this illustrious device. In this section, we shall elucidate the elementary steps to set up and install your new solar lantern in an expeditious and thoroughly meticulous manner.

3.1: Initial Setup

1. Unpacking: Carefully unbox your Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern, taking great care not to jostle or mar its pristine exterior. Gently lift the lantern from the container and examine each component for any signs of damage, ensuring they correspond with those depicted in the enclosed diagram.

2. Battery Installation: If your lantern did not arrive pre-installed with batteries, locate the battery compartment on the underside of the device (marked as A in our illustration below). Insert two AA batteries with the positive terminals facing towards the label "+" symbol. Securely close the compartment to ensure a snug fit and proper contact.

4. Operation and Maintenance


4.1 Turning the Lantern On and Off

To activate your esteemed Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern, kindly locate the circular power button situated on the lantern's top panel, towards its front end. Gently press this button once, and the lantern shall commence illuminating, gracing your surroundings with its radiant light. To turn off the lantern, simply press and hold the power button for approximately two seconds until it enters a restful slumber.


4.2 Adjusting the Brightness

For those moments when you'd prefer a softer glow or require a more brilliant beacon, your Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern offers a thoughtful adjustable brightness feature. To increase the brightness level, press and hold the "+" brightness button located on the lantern's left side. The brightness will incrementally increase. Should you find yourself in need of a less illuminated space, merely press and hold the "-" brightness button on the lantern's right side to decrease the brightness level.

4.3 Troubleshooting and Frequently Asked Questions

Should your Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern encounter any challenges during its service or provide answers to frequently asked questions, we invite you to refer to our dedicated support site at www.sunglowsupport.com or consult the user manual provided with your purchase. Therein, you shall find a wealth of knowledge and guidance designed to ensure the continued optimal performance of your solar lantern.

Important note: It is crucial to avoid exposure of the lantern to prolonged periods under direct sunlight, as excessive heat may harm the battery. Remember, our Revive XL Solar Lantern is designed for use as a camping companion or outdoor illumination source – it is not intended to be left in the sun indefinitely.

(c) Sunglow 8


5: Advanced Features and Accessories


5.1 Using USB Charging

For those instances when sunlight alone cannot recharge your lantern, the Revive XL Solar Lantern features a convenient USB charging port. To utilize this function, connect the lantern to a power source using the provided USB cable, ensuring the positive (+) side of the cable is connected to the lantern. The charging status indicator, located on the front panel, will display a solid red light during charging. Once fully charged, the indicator will switch to a steady green light.

5.2 Lantern Maintenance and Storage

To extend the longevity and maintain optimal performance of your Sunglow Revive XL Solar Lantern, we recommend regular maintenance: Clean the lantern's surface with a soft cloth and mild detergent as required, avoiding direct water exposure if possible. Store the lantern in a cool, dry place away from prolonged sunlight to ensure battery preservation and extend its lifespan.

1. Welcome to Sunglow GlowStar Solar Lanterns!


Welcome, dear Customer, to your Sunglow GlowStar 2-Pack Solar Lanterns adventure! This manual help you discover all features of your fine Solar Lanterns.


1.1 What you get in Box


In your box, you find:

1. Two (2) GlowStar Solar Lanterns, made by our respected Sunglow brand. 2. Each lantern have Adjustable Brightness Control and Motion Sensor. 3. Set include USB charging cable, for cloudy day recharge. 4. User manual, like this one, to help you start.


|Component  | Quantity| |---|---| |Solar Lanterns | 2 | |USB Charging Cable | 1 | |User Manual | 1 |

2. Prepare for First Use


2.1 Charge Before First Use


Before using your Sunglow GlowStar 2-Pack Solar Lanterns, you need to charge them first, ensure longtime working and best performance.

1. Find Sunlight: Place the solar lanterns in direct sunlight for max 7 hours, or connect to a USB power source with adapter (not included).

2. Attention: Solar panels MUST be exposed to sunlight during charging. 3. Warning! Do NOT leave the lanterns under the sun for too long as it might damage the


battery.


diagram of solar panel charging


2.2 Install Motion Sensor

Our advanced GlowStar Solar Lanterns feature a motion sensor, auto turn on at night. Set up the sensors for optimal experience.

1. Caution: Be gentle during installation to avoid damaging internal components. 2. Rotate lantern body counter-clockwise to open, revealing sensor area. 3. Adjust Sensor: Position the sensor towards desired area, allowing the best coverage

for your needs. 4. Close lantern by rotating back clockwise when finished.


diagram of motion sensor installation


2.3 Adjust Brightness


Personalize the brightness level to suit your preferences with our GlowStar Solar Lanterns.

1. Press and hold the power button for 5 seconds. 2. Click: Quick presses will increase or decrease brightness accordingly. 3. Repeat process until desired brightness is reached.


2.4 Set up Multi-Lanterns Connection


Should you wish to connect multiple solar lanterns, follow the steps below:

(c) Sunglow 5

1. Charge all lanterns individually first. 2. Connect only adjacent lanterns using the provided wires. 3. Repeat step 2 until all lanterns are connected in a chain-like manner. 4. Enjoy your illuminated space!

4.1: Charge with Sunlight

Bring your Sunglow GlowStar 2-Pack Solar Lanterns under sunlight full day, minimum. Maximize exposure to solar panel, located on top of lantern. Kindly note: charging process may take longer during winter or cloudy weather.

5. TroubleShooting


5.1: The Lanterns Won't Light Up!


If your GlowStar 2-Pack Solar Lanterns from Sunglow not working, try next steps:

1. Check battery level: Press button on each lantern for 3 seconds, light will blink, show battery status. If red, recharge!

2. Sunlight or USB: Charge under sunlight > 5 hours or connect to USB > 8 hours. No power source? Try both methods!

3. Clean Solar Panels: Remove dirt, debris from solar panels with soft cloth and water. 4. Check connections: Make sure all wires securely connected, no loose parts. 5. Factory reset: Press both buttons simultaneously > 10 seconds, release, repeat.


5.2: The Brightness is Wrong!


If GlowStar lanterns' brightness not to your satisfaction, try these steps:

1. Change brightness level: Press the button until desired brightness is reached (Press longer for higher levels).

2. Check solar panel positioning: Ensure solar panels face the sun directly for optimal charging and performance.

3. Daylight vs. Nighttime: Brightness may vary depending on whether it's day or night.


5.3: Motion Sensor Not Working!


If GlowStar lanterns' motion sensor failing to detect motion, try these solutions:

1. Sensor cleaning: Clean the motion sensor with a soft, dry cloth. Avoid water exposure. 2. "Test" the sensor: Perform quick movements around the sensor area for approximately

30 seconds and observe if lantern activates. 3. "Re-calibrate" sensor: Wait for one hour without any movement detection to allow


sensor to recalibrate.
